<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-24T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-24T16:00:00-05:00" n="1408" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1408">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.34112A/8–2144: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reed</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-24T17:00:00-04:00">August 24,
                                    1944—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>269. Proposal regarding Colegio Alemán contained in urtel 474, August 21,
                            7 p.m., satisfactory to Department. You are authorized to accept
                            proposal stipulating 1) immediate removal of Ketterer, 2) his relegation
                            to restricted area, 3) appointment of Paraguayan to handle school
                            finances, 4) further action in eliminating other objectionable elements
                            November 15.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>